      "writtenOn": "2017-07-18T03:33:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I’m concerned that this interface requires callers to check is_valid() on all of the threads it gets via ProcessReader::Threads(). Seems cumbersome when we can just not populate the thread list with bogus data in the first place (and instead log an error). What do we do on other platforms? How were you planning on calling into this to make your ProcessSnapshot/ThreadSnapshot?",
      "revId": "16bcf1e01044e139fc60dbd2152eb7f21cdcfa53",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
