        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-07-19T04:51:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hrm, this could be tricky and will depend on what kinds of things we expect to use the TLS for. This address will point to different things for glibc and bionic.\n\nFor bionic, it points to an array of BIONIC_TLS_SLOTS pointers.\nThe array:\nhttps://cs.corp.google.com/aosp-master/bionic/libc/bionic/pthread_internal.h?rcl\u003da571e9e7486afcb18ba6acb3b36b463002a5a923\u0026l\u003d103\nThe slots:\nhttps://cs.corp.google.com/aosp-master/bionic/libc/private/bionic_tls.h?rcl\u003da571e9e7486afcb18ba6acb3b36b463002a5a923\u0026l\u003d56\n\nFor glibc, it typically points to the struct pthread.",
